DE-AC04-94AL85000 with Sandia Corporation, the U.S. Government retains
certain rights in this software.  This software is distributed under
the GNU General Public License.

LAMMPS stands for Large-scale Atomic/Molecular Massively Parallel
Simulator.

This LAMMPS 2001 version has been superceded by more current versions.
See the LAMMPS WWW Site at
http://www.cs.sandia.gov/~sjplimp/lammps.html for more information.

LAMMPS is a classical molecular dynamics simulation code designed to
run efficiently on parallel computers.  It was developed at Sandia
National Laboratories, a US Department of Energy facility, with
funding from the DOE.

The primary author and contact for LAMMPS is Steve Plimpton, who can
be contacted at sjplimp@sandia.gov.

The LAMMPS 2001 distribution includes the following files and
directories:

README			this file
LICENSE			the GNU General Public License (GPL)
doc			documentation
src			source code
examples		test problems and output
tools			additional pre- and post-processing tools
converters		tools for converting to/from LAMMPS format

See the doc/README.txt or doc/README.html files for information on how
to make and use LAMMPS.
